    "Body": " Hotel Controller Key Responsibilities The Hotel Controller will be responsible for the financial affairs of several citizenM hotels based in the US, which includes reporting, analysis, payroll, taxes and cashflow projections. He or she will supervise outsourced administrations on bookkeeping and Purchase-to-Pay and solve related issues. Main tasks Monthly close (Management P&L) for citizenM hotel operations in New York and Boston. Seattle and Washington D.C. will follow in the second quarter of 2020 Participate in monthly analytical P&L meetings with our Support Office, based in The Netherlands and with our US management teams, based in New York Quarterly reporting package of the US hotel operations entities, to report in citizenM\u2019s financial systems Tagetik and Blackline Provide analytical support and decision-making tools to hotel leadership team and department heads to help achieve desired business results Financial assistance in the pre-opening phase of new citizenM hotels in Seattle, Washington D.C., Los Angeles, Miami, San Francisco, Chicago and Boston Monitor implementation and compliance of company financial policies and procedures Manage Purchase-to-Pay process solving issues and implementing improvements Assist in local tax filings Oversee payroll, which is processed in ADP by hotel managers and HR Give input for cashflow forecasting Qualifications / Skills Bsc or Msc in Finance / Accounting / Economics At least 3 - 5 years of experience in Finance & Accounting Strong communication skills Excellent computer skills Ability to work well as part of the citizenM US Finance Team Knowledge of Microsoft Dynamics NAV and Blackline is an advantage Ability to travel to the hotels outside of New York (on average once or twice per month) Proactive, flexible and independent ", 
